    "summary": "Learn about the common early signs of pregnancy and understand which symptoms may appear before a missed period.",
    "content": "# Early Pregnancy Signs\n\nEvery pregnancy is unique. Some people notice symptoms very early, while others may not experience any noticeable changes for several weeks.\n\nUnderstanding early pregnancy signs can help you recognize changes happening in your body.\n\n## Why Symptoms Occur\n\nAfter fertilization and implantation, the body begins producing a hormone called Human Chorionic Gonadotropin (hCG).\n\nThis hormone supports pregnancy and contributes to many early symptoms.\n\n## Common Early Signs\n\n### Missed Period\n\nA missed period is often the first noticeable sign of pregnancy.\n\nHowever, cycle irregularities can occur for other reasons, including stress, illness, and hormonal changes.\n\n### Fatigue\n\nMany people experience unusual tiredness during early pregnancy.\n\nHormonal changes and increased energy demands contribute to this fatigue.\n\n### Breast Changes\n\nBreasts may become:\n\n• Tender\n• Swollen\n• Sensitive\n• Heavier than usual\n\n### Nausea\n\nMorning sickness can occur at any time of day.\n\nSome people experience nausea as early as a few weeks after conception.\n\n### Frequent Urination\n\nHormonal changes increase blood flow to the kidneys, leading to more frequent trips to the bathroom.\n\n### Mood Changes\n\nHormone fluctuations may affect mood and emotional sensitivity.\n\n### Food Cravings Or Aversions\n\nCertain foods may suddenly become appealing or unpleasant.\n\n## Symptoms Before A Missed Period\n\nSome people notice:\n\n• Mild cramping\n• Implantation spotting\n• Breast tenderness\n• Fatigue\n• Increased sensitivity to smells\n\n## When To Take A Pregnancy Test\n\nHome pregnancy tests are generally most accurate after a missed period.\n\nTesting too early may result in a false negative.\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: Morning sickness only happens in the morning.\n\nFact: Pregnancy-related nausea can occur at any time of day.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nEarly pregnancy signs can include fatigue, breast tenderness, nausea, frequent urination, mood changes, and a missed period. Symptoms vary greatly between individuals and pregnancies."
