    "summary": "Understand how nutrition supports energy, circulation, hormonal health, and overall sexual wellbeing.",
    "content": "# Nutrition & Sexual Wellness\n\nSexual wellbeing is influenced by physical, emotional, and social factors.\n\nNutrition is one factor that supports overall health and may contribute to healthy energy levels and body function.\n\n## The Connection Between Nutrition And Sexual Wellness\n\nThe body relies on nutrients to support:\n\n• Blood circulation\n• Hormone production\n• Energy levels\n• Mood\n• General health\n\n## Nutrients That Support Overall Health\n\n### Healthy Fats\n\nHealthy fats are important for hormone production.\n\nSources include:\n\n• Nuts\n• Seeds\n• Avocados\n• Olive oil\n• Fatty fish\n\n### Protein\n\nProtein supports tissue repair and overall body function.\n\nSources include:\n\n• Eggs\n• Dairy products\n• Poultry\n• Beans\n• Lentils\n\n### Fruits And Vegetables\n\nFruits and vegetables provide vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants.\n\nAim for a variety of colorful options.\n\n### Hydration\n\nWater supports circulation, energy, and normal body function.\n\n## Lifestyle Factors Matter Too\n\nSexual wellness is not only about food.\n\nImportant factors include:\n\n• Sleep\n• Physical activity\n• Mental wellbeing\n• Healthy relationships\n• Communication\n\n## Understanding Sexual Health\n\nSexual health includes:\n\n• Physical wellbeing\n• Emotional wellbeing\n• Respectful relationships\n• Consent\n• Protection from sexually transmitted infections\n\n## Common Myth\n\nMyth: Certain foods instantly improve sexual performance.\n\nFact: No food creates immediate dramatic changes. Long-term healthy habits support overall wellbeing.\n\n## Quick Summary\n\nNutrition supports overall health, hormone production, circulation, and energy levels. Healthy eating is one part of maintaining sexual wellness and wellbeing."
